article.headline: Southern Utah 67, Idaho 50
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah (AP) -- Nurudeen Adepoju scored 13 points and Justin Allen added 12, as Southern Utah beat Idaho 67-50 Wednesday night. Steve Barnes scored 10 points for the Thunderbirds (3-1), who shot 50 percent from the field and outrebounded the Vandals 38-25. Keoni Watson led Idaho (1-3) with 12 points, while Desmond Nwoke had 11. Southern Utah took a 10-8 lead on Orlando Griego's layup off the offensive board five minutes into the game and didn't trail after that. The Thunderbird's stiff defense forced 12 Idaho turnovers and held the Vandals to seven field goals in the first half. During a pivotal 18-4 run that began with 9:34 to play in the half, Allen and Barnes each hit 3-pointers, and Allen gave Southern Utah a double-digit lead, 23-13, with a coast-to-coast layup off a steal. Meanwhile, the Vandals went nearly three minutes without a field goal before Mario Mackey hit a turnaround jumper in the key at 6:40. After that, Idaho managed two free throws over the next four minutes. By the time Watson broke the drought with a layup at 2:01, the Thunderbirds led 34-19. Adepoju hit a 3-pointer from the left corner early in the second half to push the margin to 43-23. Marcus Carson scored off a fast break to give Southern Utah its biggest lead, 62-37, with 6:26 to play.
